The ~/.vimrc and ~/.vim content are following 
Tamar Saleh's blog post at 
http://tammersaleh.com/posts/the-modern-vim-config-with-pathogen

One thing to note:
	at the file ~/.vim/update_bundle, the first line (shebang)
	should point to your ruby bin of choice. In my case, I am using 
	rvm. Hence, it is pointing to the ruby 1.9.2 in the rvm path
